CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 21, 1954, pg. 24, reads: "Primed for Play-Offs - The booming bats and capable mound staff of the Terrace Village baseball team are shown above ready for the first game of the championship play-offs in the Greater Pittsburgh League. The Villagers meet North Pittsburgh tonight (Thursday) at North's Field. Front row, left to right, are hurlers Fount Dickerson, Mel Brown, 'Doc' Shanafelt, Harry Weathers and Jack Shea. Back row: C. Hull, G. King, J. Watts, J. McElroy, K. Zeno, A. Gregory, B. Hull, W. Brown and J. Williamson. Not shown are Maurice Peatross and Ralph McNeal. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Terrace Village baseball team members, first row from left: Fount Dickerson, Mel Brown, 'Doc' Shanafelt, Harry Weathers, Jack Shea; back row: C. Hull, G. King, J. Watts, J. McElroy, K. Zeno, A. Gregory, B. Hull, W. Brown and J. Williamson posed on Kennard Field
